de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.flow.defUseChains
Class DefUseChains

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.flow.defUseChains.DefUseChains
Direct Known Subclasses:
DefUseChainsInitial
public class DefUseChains
extends java.lang.Object

This Class represents the def-use chains generated for a method and any invoked method (according to the options set). There can be multiple DefUseChains containing chains for a Method, but only one per distinct initial Method which is presented by the sub class DefUseChainsInitial.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-16
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

Method Detail

addDefUseChain

boolean addDefUseChain(DefUseChain defUseChain)
Add a def use chain. If it already is included, it will not be included twice and false will be returned.

This method has package visibility, as only the DuGenerator should add def-use chains.

Parameters:
defUseChain - The def-use chain to add.
Returns:
true, if it was added, false if it already is added.

removeDefUseChain
